commit.message: Write photo hash to disk, added options to refresh them
Added support for pickling photo hashes and to skip metadata update if photo is cached
Fixed typo, fixed wrong parameter to photo.update()
Remove tags before adding new one
Added tags support. Make photos private by default
Added support for comparing hashed before uploading
Added first draft of the importer
Added support to configure debug at the httplib level
Added options to configure logging for requests
Added objects to the shell enviroment. Added help
Added first version of the shell script.
First, quick, cheap version of the downloader using pyopenphoto
Added support for python 3.2 in travisCI
added support for py32 in tests
Removed dependency from openphoto. Added initial support for tox and tests
Added a wrapper around requests to authenticate and use host from config
Changed run wrapper API: config now is a mandatory param
Added wrapper to handle common exceptions in scripts
Added argument parsing and client creation
Added host config, renamed section to "api"
